{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K2rouCF3mxPayXa1prbMfB","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d94a92ae-93cf-430a-a395-7caa50486212","uuid":"644f53bf-54ea-4da9-b01f-ac00c2a7719d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:39:55.264Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":37,"newStart":1,"newLines":1,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23","-","-### 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:15Z)","-","-- **Code quality concern:** Cargo.toml parsing uses simple string `includes()` matching, not a proper TOML parser. Per NFR4, but a dependency name in a comment or `[dev-dependencies]` would false-positive (e.g., `# we considered using axum` triggers server detection).","-- **Observation:** Existing test for \"unrecognized stack\" was using `'rust'` as unrecognized — changed to `'java'`.","-- **Observation:** AC4 maps library crates to `generic` AppType rather than new `'library'` type — deliberate design choice but means library crates are indistinguishable from unknown projects.","-","-### 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T09:25Z)","-","-- **HIGH fixed:** `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps — false positive agent/server detection. Added `getCargoDepsSection()` to extract only `[dependencies]` section.","-- **HIGH fixed:** Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`, `rocket` matching `sprocket`). Added `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments. Used line-anchored regexes.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks (rocket, tide, warp).","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` dual-crate pattern.","-- **LOW unfixed:** `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML style. Acceptable per NFR4.","-- **Coverage:** 97.02% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No integration test for detectStack→detectAppType end-to-end (acceptable — unit tested independently).","-","-### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)","-","-- **Observation:** Story spec said `coverage.tool` was `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'unknown'` but it was actually a plain `string` in `HarnessState`. Tightened to proper union — non-breaking.","-- **Observation:** ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, etc.). Unrelated to this story. Tests pass at runtime via Vitest despite `tsc --noEmit` errors.","-","-### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — code-review (2026-03-23T09:28Z)","-","-- **HIGH fixed:** `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack. Rust projects got wrong default.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch — Cargo.toml projects fell through to `'unknown'`.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md mislabeled Rust projects.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate.","-- **LOW unfixed:** `getCoverageTool()` in docs-scaffold.ts and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` in state.ts duplicate stack-to-tool mapping.","-- **Coverage gap:** `parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser — out of scope for 8-2 (story 8-3 will address).","-","-### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T09:32Z)","-","-- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust_env_hint` never written to state — `instrumentProject()` returned early for Rust with \"Unsupported stack\". Fixed by adding Rust branch to `instrumentProject()` and `rust_env_hint` to `configureOtlpEnvVars()`.","-- **Re-verification needed:** Time budget exhausted before Docker re-verification. Story left at `verifying` — next session will re-verify.","-- **Flaky test observation:** One vitest run showed 1 failed/2968 passed, next run showed 0 failed/2969 passed. Could not identify which test was flaky — output was mixed with Ink rendering control codes."]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n\n### 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:15Z)\n\n- **Code quality concern:** Cargo.toml parsing uses simple string `includes()` matching, not a proper TOML parser. Per NFR4, but a dependency name in a comment or `[dev-dependencies]` would false-positive (e.g., `# we considered using axum` triggers server detection).\n- **Observation:** Existing test for \"unrecognized stack\" was using `'rust'` as unrecognized — changed to `'java'`.\n- **Observation:** AC4 maps library crates to `generic` AppType rather than new `'library'` type — deliberate design choice but means library crates are indistinguishable from unknown projects.\n\n### 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T09:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps — false positive agent/server detection. Added `getCargoDepsSection()` to extract only `[dependencies]` section.\n- **HIGH fixed:** Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`, `rocket` matching `sprocket`). Added `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments. Used line-anchored regexes.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks (rocket, tide, warp).\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` dual-crate pattern.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML style. Acceptable per NFR4.\n- **Coverage:** 97.02% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No integration test for detectStack→detectAppType end-to-end (acceptable — unit tested independently).\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)\n\n- **Observation:** Story spec said `coverage.tool` was `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'unknown'` but it was actually a plain `string` in `HarnessState`. Tightened to proper union — non-breaking.\n- **Observation:** ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, etc.). Unrelated to this story. Tests pass at runtime via Vitest despite `tsc --noEmit` errors.\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — code-review (2026-03-23T09:28Z)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack. Rust projects got wrong default.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch — Cargo.toml projects fell through to `'unknown'`.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md mislabeled Rust projects.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `getCoverageTool()` in docs-scaffold.ts and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` in state.ts duplicate stack-to-tool mapping.\n- **Coverage gap:** `parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser — out of scope for 8-2 (story 8-3 will address).\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T09:32Z)\n\n- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust_env_hint` never written to state — `instrumentProject()` returned early for Rust with \"Unsupported stack\". Fixed by adding Rust branch to `instrumentProject()` and `rust_env_hint` to `configureOtlpEnvVars()`.\n- **Re-verification needed:** Time budget exhausted before Docker re-verification. Story left at `verifying` — next session will re-verify.\n- **Flaky test observation:** One vitest run showed 1 failed/2968 passed, next run showed 0 failed/2969 passed. Could not identify which test was flaky — output was mixed with Ink rendering control codes.\n"}}
